# React Blog App

## Description

This project demonstrates React Class Components and Lifecycle Methods by fetching blog posts from a REST API and displaying them in the browser.

## Technologies Used

- React
- JavaScript (ES6)
- HTML
- CSS
- Node.js
- npm

## Features

- Class Component
- componentDidMount()
- componentDidCatch()
- REST API Integration
- Display Blog Posts

## Project Structure

```
blogapp
│
├── src
│   ├── Posts.js
│   ├── Post.js
│   ├── App.js
│   └── index.js
```

## API Used

https://jsonplaceholder.typicode.com/posts

## Installation

```bash
git clone https://github.com/your-username/blogapp.git
cd blogapp
npm install
npm start
```

## Learning Outcomes

- React Class Components
- React Lifecycle Methods
- Fetching Data from REST API
- Error Handling with componentDidCatch()
- Rendering Dynamic Data
